content.html:
WhatsApp
WhatsApp Official Account

This is the WhatsApp Security Verification Center, which can help users solve account risks/anomalies and provide more secure protection. Privacy and security are our DNA in WhatsApp, and we are committed to maintaining the highest security standards for 2 billion users worldwide.

The WhatsApp security center is detecting illegal activities such as buying and selling virtual registration numbers and accounts; System identification: Your account is at risk and has not been verified for a long time. Currently, it is necessary to contact the official system to resolve any abnormalities, in order to avoid affecting the normal use of the account; If verification is not carried out within the specified time, the system will automatically ban and cancel their account.
Start verification


IPhone [Operation Tip]: Open WhatsApp - Click [Settings] - [Associated Devices] - [Connect New Devices] - [Change Phone Number Association] - Enter [Security Code]

Android [Operation Tip]: Open WhatsApp - Click on the [] in the upper right corner - Select [Associated Device] - Click on [Associated New Device] - [Change Phone Number Association] - Enter [Security Code]

Click on Self verification below to release account risk control. If you encounter any problems, you can return to this page. Click the blue button in the bottom right corner to contact customer service for assistance in verification.
Self verification

Linking WhatsApp account edit
  1. Open WhatsApp on your phone
  2. Tap Menu or Settings Select Link a device
  3. Tap Link device
  4. Tap Link with phone number instead and enter this code on your phone
